CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 25, 1961, pg. 17, reads: "At Stanley's Lounge - The famous Evelyn Childress Combo is now playing nightly with her on organ; Fred Pryor, drums; Clarence Oden, alto sax. You can stop right now making those laborious Thanksgiving plans.  Just dial CH. 1-9585 or CH1-9846 and let Stanley know how many will be coming out or one of his delicious Thanksgiving dinners.  Stanley's is conveniently located at 7403 Frankstown Ave. at Collier St., Homewood."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of the Lady Evelyn Childress Organ Trio, including Fred Pryor on drums, Clarence Oden on saxophone, and Evelyn Childress on organ, posed in club with mirror and television in background
